  "answer": "## Answer\nAcross the sources, the recurring failure modes in multi-agent systems are: coordination overhead, role confusion, error propagation, consensus without correctness, and evaluation difficulty. Some are stated explicitly in framework docs and empirical papers; others are reasonable engineering inferences from the failure patterns described there. ([arxiv.org](https://arxiv.org/abs/2501.06322))\n\n### Required aspect coverage\n- coordination overhead — covered: hierarchical supervisors, delegation, and message-history control add orchestration cost, and CrewAI flags excessive back-and-forth as a problem. ([docs.crewai.com](https://docs.crewai.com/concepts/collaboration))\n- role confusion — covered: CrewAI explicitly warns against vague/overlapping roles and recommends clear role definitions and responsibilities. ([docs.crewai.com](https://docs.crewai.com/concepts/collaboration))\n- error propagation — covered: the consensus-trap paper shows that flawed intermediate logic can survive into final answers when aggregation is vote-based. ([arxiv.org](https://arxiv.org/abs/2604.17139))\n- consensus without correctness — covered: both the consensus-trap paper and DEBATE show that agreement or convergence can still be wrong. ([arxiv.org](https://arxiv.org/abs/2604.17139))\n- evaluation difficulty — covered: DEBATE and the evaluation paper both show that multi-agent behavior is hard to benchmark and that many answer paths complicate reliable assessment. ([arxiv.org](https://arxiv.org/abs/2510.25110))\n\n## Sources\n- Survey: Multi-Agent Collaboration Mechanisms: A Survey of LLMs. ([arxiv.org](https://arxiv.org/abs/2501.06322))\n- Official docs: CrewAI collaboration troubleshooting and best practices. ([docs.crewai.com](https://docs.crewai.com/concepts/collaboration))\n- Official docs: LangGraph multi-agent supervisor. ([langchain-ai.github.io](https://langchain-ai.github.io/langgraphjs/reference/modules/langgraph-supervisor.html))\n- Empirical failure analysis: The Consensus Trap. ([arxiv.org](https://arxiv.org/abs/2604.17139))\n- Benchmark: DEBATE. ([arxiv.org](https://arxiv.org/abs/2510.25110))\n- Evaluation paper: On Evaluating the Integration of Reasoning and Action in LLM Agents. ([arxiv.org](https://arxiv.org/pdf/2311.09721))\n\n## Limitations\nThe evidence is strongest for LLM-based multi-agent systems, not every kind of multi-agent system. Also, \"coordination overhead\" and \"role confusion\" are partly inferred from framework troubleshooting guidance rather than always named as formal failure modes in the papers. Finally, consensus is shown to be an unreliable proxy for truth, but some tasks may still benefit from consensus as a heuristic. ([docs.crewai.com](https://docs.crewai.com/concepts/collaboration))"
